article.headline: Creighton 77, Colorado 72
article.story:
OMAHA, Neb. (AP) -- Kristi Woodard scored 26 points and grabbed
five rebounds to lead Creighton to a 77-72 win over Colorado on
Saturday.

Angie Janis added 21 points, eight rebounds and six assists in
the win for Creighton (2-2).

Jasmina Ilic scored 26 points and Jackie MacFarland had 23 to
lead Colorado (2-4) in the loss. MacFarland also pulled down 12
rebounds and dished out four assists.

Creighton scored 21 points off of 15 Colorado turnovers.
